82675 82675 Give reasoning steps and answers. There is a regular pentagon in the diagram, represented by the symbol VYJFA. What is the measure of each internal angle of this pentagon?
Since VYJFA is a regular pentagon, all its internal angles are equal. A regular pentagon has 5 equal internal angles, and the sum of all internal angles in any polygon is (n-2)*180 degrees, where n is the number of sides. For a pentagon, n=5, so the sum is (5-2)*180 = 540 degrees. Therefore, each internal angle of a regular pentagon is 540/5 = 108 degrees.
